Kaduna &mdash; A group under the aegis of Search for Common Ground, in partnership with Justice Development and Peace Commission with support from United States Agency for International Development (USAID), has organized a one-day inter-community dialogue for farmers and pastoralist communities of Southern Kaduna to establishing unity among them.Speaking at the event, the senior program manager of Search for Common Ground, Sani Suleiman, said the organization sought to build the capacity of communities as well as support them to find common ground on issues of conflict.